[{"id":"VR802578","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a positively charged particle and two parallel plates that are oriented vertically. The left plate is positively charged, and the right plate is negatively charged. Between the two plates is a uniform magnetic field with magnitude B directed into the page. Arrows indicate that the charged particle moves horizontally left to right toward the magnetic field, and then upon entering the magnetic field between the plates the particle moves upward and to the right at an angle theta with the horizontal.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR802578.g02.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A positively charged particle moves with speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v\"><math alttext=\"v\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>v</mi></math></span></span> into the region between two parallel plates. The left plate is positively charged and the right plate is negatively charged to produce an electric field with magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E\"><math alttext=\"E\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>E</mi></math></span></span>. A uniform magnetic field <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>B</mi></math></span></span> directed into the page exists between the plates. Which of the following is a correct equation that could be used to determine the angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\"><math alttext=\"theta\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span> relative to the horizontal of the sum of forces on the particle immediately after it enters the region? Gravitational effects can be ignored.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR802578_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the tangent of theta equals, the fraction E over B\"><math alttext=\"the tangent of theta equals, the fraction E over B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>tan</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>E</mi><mi>B</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the tangent of theta equals, the fraction B over E\"><math alttext=\"the tangent of theta equals, the fraction B over E\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>tan</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>B</mi><mi>E</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the tangent of theta equals, the fraction E over v B\"><math alttext=\"the tangent of theta equals, the fraction E over v B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>tan</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>E</mi><mrow><mi>v</mi><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the tangent of theta equals, the fraction v B over E\"><math alttext=\"the tangent of theta equals, the fraction v B over E\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>tan</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>v</mi><mi>B</mi></mrow><mi>E</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":3}]